    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look for stability today, with **Jackson Merrill** (65.98) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.81) serving as our offensive pillars. **Jackson Merrill** benefits significantly from a favorable platoon split against right-hander Luis Castillo, while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** continues to project well based on a strong .384 xwOBA, keeping him in the lineup despite a slight dip due to platoon dynamics against Sproat. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.68) remains a high-floor play at second base; his aggressive positioning at the top of the order combined with a 14% boost from a favorable right-handed platoon matchup makes him an essential start. Conversely, **Gunnar Henderson** (48.62) faces a tough outing against Messick; while his base profile is high, the combination of an elite skill matchup and significant platoon disadvantage creates a drag on his efficiency, further compounded by a 36% rain risk.\n\nThe decision to bench **Nolan Schanuel** (47.95) was the tightest call on the board today. While **Nolan Schanuel** offers a solid plate approach, his projected efficiency fell just short of **Miguel Vargas** (49.72), who retains value today primarily due to his spot at the top of the lineup. We are also monitoring the bench closely regarding **Nasim Nunez** (42.25); despite his elite sprint speed\u2014a core priority for our stolen base targets\u2014his low spot in the batting order and the presence of a pitcher in Ashcraft who holds runners effectively significantly dampened his score, keeping him on the sidelines. We will continue to monitor weather updates in Messick's game, as any escalation in the rain risk for **Gunnar Henderson** or **Coby Mayo** could necessitate a quick pivot before the first pitch.",
